the design and performance of database systems. In this paper, we present one of the
first experimental studies on characterizing Intel® Optane™ DC PMM's performance behavior
in the context of analytical database workloads. First, we analyze basic access patterns
common in such workloads, such as sequential, selective, and random reads as well
as the complete Star Schema Benchmark, comparing standalone DRAM- and PMem-based implementations.
Then we extend our analysis to join algorithms over larger datasets, which require
using DRAM and PMem in a hybrid fashion while paying special attention to the read-write
asymmetry of PMem. Our study reveals interesting performance tradeoffs that can help
guide the design of next-generation OLAP systems in presence of persistent memory
in the storage hierarchy.},
