abstract = {Motivated by contemporary security challenges, we reevaluate and refine capability-based
addressing for the RISC era. We present CHERI, a hybrid capability model that extends
the 64-bit MIPS ISA with byte-granularity memory protection. We demonstrate that CHERI
enables language memory model enforcement and fault isolation in hardware rather than
software, and that the CHERI mechanisms are easily adopted by existing programs for
